      <p class="mb-6">
        Surge protection is a safety mechanism designed to block or redirect excess voltage that can come from power grid fluctuations, lightning strikes, or internal switching events. Surge protection devices provide overvoltage protection by diverting transient overvoltages away from sensitive equipment.
      </p>
      <p>
        These surges, often caused by transient overvoltages and transient overvoltage events, can damage or destroy modern appliances, electronics, and even fire alarms or security systems. Protection against transient overvoltages is a key function of a surge protection device.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

