      </p>
      <p>
        Surge protection devices are specifically engineered to shield your electrical systems from these unpredictable events by diverting dangerous voltage away from your valuable equipment. For even greater security, a lightning protection system (LPS) can be installed, which includes air terminals, down conductors, and earth electrodes to safely channel lightning energy away from your building. Combining an LPS with surge protectors at your main distribution board and at individual devices ensures layered protection against both direct and indirect lightning strikes, keeping your systems and equipment safe from harm.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

