      </p>
      <p class="mt-4">
        In certain configurations, especially with overhead lines and TT networks, surge protection devices may include a neutral pole equipped with a gas tube. This setup helps prevent earth faults and enhances overall system safety.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4">
        The type of surge protection device and installation method may vary depending on factors such as whether the supply is via overhead lines, the supply current, and the configuration of consumer units and circuit breakers. Selecting the appropriate device and installation approach ensures optimal protection and compliance with regulations.
